{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "The Benefits of Wisdom"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "My son, if you accept my words and hide my commandments within you,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "if you incline your ear to wisdom and direct your heart to understanding,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "if you truly call out to insight and lift your voice to understanding,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "if you seek it like silver and search it out like hidden treasure,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "then you will discern the fear of the LORD and discover the knowledge of God."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For the LORD gives wisdom; from His mouth come knowledge and understanding."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He stores up sound wisdom for the upright; He is a shield to those who walk with integrity,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "to guard the paths of justice and protect the way of His saints."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then you will discern righteousness and justice and equity—every good path."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For wisdom will enter your heart, and knowledge will delight your soul."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Discretion will watch over you, and understanding will guard you,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "to deliver you from the way of evil, from the man who speaks perversity,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "from those who leave the straight pathsto walk in the ways of darkness,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "from those who enjoy doing evil and rejoice in the twistedness of evil,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "whose paths are crooked and whose ways are devious."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "It will rescue you from the forbidden woman,[^4] from the stranger[^5] with seductive words"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "law",
          "text": "who abandons the partner of her youth and forgets the covenant of her God."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For her house sinks down to death, and her tracks to the departed spirits.[^6]"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "None who go to her returnor negotiate the paths of life."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "So you will follow in the ways of the good, and keep to the paths of the righteous."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For the upright will inhabit the land, and the blameless will remain in it;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "but the wicked will be cut off from the land, and the unfaithful will be uprooted."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}